{"questionId":"14345","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A group of 7 adult men wanted to see if there was a relationship between their Body Mass Index (BMI) and their waist size. Their waist sizes, in centimetres, were recorded and their BMI calculated. The following table shows the results.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/8a49ffc98624c7eb7ea169207c9d3ec39c6653e0.png\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">The relationship between <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span> and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n</math></span> can be modelled by the regression equation <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = ax + b\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the correlation coefficient.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>0.977563</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"r\">\n  <mi>r</mi>\n</math></span> = 0.978&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1 N1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"14345","referenceCode":"19M.2.SL.TZ2.S_1a.ii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the correlation coefficient.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.4—Pearsons, scatter diagrams, eqn of y on x"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}